President Obama announced his intent to nominate Tim Broas as the Ambassador to the Kingdom of the Netherlands and Richard L. Morningstar as the Ambassador to the Republic of Azerbaijan. He also announced his intent to appoint Nancy Hellman Bechtle as a member of the Board of Directors of the Presidio Trust, Reginald Dwayne Betts as a member of the Coordinating Council on Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention, and Patricia G. Smith as a member of the Advisory Board of the National Air and Space Museum. The President believes that these individuals will be valuable additions to his administration as they work together to address the challenges facing America.